story: MIT African Students' Association - ASA is with Nonye Ikeanyi and 11 others.
message: McCormick Dining served African cuisine today. Among others, it served Yassa chicken, Kenyan corn and beans, spinach peanut stew, Nigerian jollof rice, South African bobotie, and Tunisian chick pea soup. It is lucid from the smiles on the faces that the community dinner today went superbly, although, as usual, there were dashes of heated jollof arguments.
